        "abstract": "United States Immunodeficiency Network (USIDNET) is a NIAID supported IID repository that includes clinical data.",
        "description": "The United States Immunodeficiency Network (USIDNET) is a research consortium established to advance scientific research in the field of immunodeficiencies/inborn errors of immunity. We have several goals:\n\n   - Collection of phenotype data using automated data extraction to populate a freely accessible registry\n   - Facilitation of studies on outcomes and phenotypes using USIDNET data\n   - Matchmaking services to connect clinicians and researchers\n   - Collaboration with ClinGen, OMIM, MONDO and HPO to improve data in other databases\n   - Development of do-it-yourself (DIY) data access points\n   - Mentoring of trainees",
